{title: We're Steppin' Out Tonight}
{artist: David Ball}
{composer: Written by Billy Wallace}

[G7]Let folks call us gadabouts
Cause tonight we're steppin’ [C]out
[F]Oh we're steppin’ out tonight
[C]We'll go where the lights are bright
I'll [F]hold you in my arms so tight
We [C]won't come home till [G7]dawn
On [C]fifty cents worth of gasoline
I'll drive the ol’ Ford like a Limousine
With the [G7]fender smashed and one light out
Cause tonight we're steppin’ [C]out
With two hot dogs and a coke for you
Maybe I'll rate a glass of brew
[G7]We'll get happy we'll sing and shout
Cause tonight we're steppin’ [C]out
We'll go to a tavern and cut a rug
I'll hold you while you jitterbug
[G7]One cuts in and ones left out
Cause tonight we're steppin’ [C]out
Repeat #3,4
[G7]Cause tonight we’re steppin’ [C]out